Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createGuide(25.10)                                          createGuide(25.10)

Name
       createGuide

Syntax
       createGuide

       [-help]

       obj_name

       box

       Creates a guide for a module or a group. Use this command after import-
       ing the design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each createGuide parameter. For a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man createGuide

       <obj_name>
              Specifies the name of the module or group to be guided.

              Data_type: string, required

       <box>  Specifies the constraints of the box.

              * llx: Specifies the lower left x coordinate of the guide area.

              * lly: Specifies the lower left y coordinate of the guide area.

              * urx: Specifies the upper right x coordinate of the guide area.

              * ury: Specifies the upper right y coordinate of the guide area.

              Data_type: box, required

Examples
              * The  following  command  creates  a  guide   for   module   of
                DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST:

                createGuide   DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST  731.28  542.08  1105.5
                829.36

                Before placement (Floorplan view)

                After placement (Physical view):

              * The following command creates a guide for group adder1:

                createGuide adder1 834.2000 1012.0000 2498.4000 3087.0000

Related Information
              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

                * Module Constraint Types

